Global Industrial Data Acquisitions Systems Market Insights
Industrial Data Acquisitions Systems Market size was valued at USD 5.32 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 9.08 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.0% from 2024 to 2030.

Industrial Data Acquisitions Systems Market Overview
The global Industrial Data Acquisitions Systems (IDAS) market was valued at USD 7.3 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 10.6 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.4% during the forecast period. The market growth is attributed to the increasing demand for real-time data analytics, the rise of automation in industries, and the adoption of Industry 4.0 technologies. The adoption of smart sensors and IoT integration further enhances the potential of data acquisition systems across diverse sectors such as manufacturing, oil & gas, and utilities. With the expansion of industrial Internet of Things (IIoT), the IDAS market is poised for substantial growth in the coming years.

